defs.name: Compute
defs.docs:
Used in actions to compute a new SPValue.
 When using delay and fetching a value from another variable, the current value of that
 variable will be taken and assigned to the action variable after the delay, and not the
 value that the other has after the delay.

defs.name: states
defs.docs: SPState represents a state in SP

defs.name: SPState
defs.docs:
Representing a State in SP with variables and their values. This is used by the runner
 and predicates and actions. This should not be sent out, instead use State

defs.name: StateExternal
defs.docs: Representing a State in SP that is shared to others and is used for sending state

defs.name: AssignState
defs.docs: Representing variables that should be assigned to a SPState. Just a wrapper to simplify life

defs.name: StateValue
defs.docs:
StateValue wrapps the value of a variable in a state. SPValue are the normal type
 and Delay and next are mainly used in the runner.

defs.name: AssignStateValue
defs.docs:
AssignStateValue is used when assigning a new value to the state
 It will either result in a Next or a delay

defs.name: Delay
defs.docs:
Delaying a next value change in actions. This will be included in the state
 and after the delay, the Delay will be replaced by the new_value in the state.

defs.name: sub_state
defs.docs: Extract a clone of the sub part of the state where the variables are children to the path

defs.name: is_sub_state_the_same
defs.docs:
Checks if a sub state is the same as another states sub state given the same path
 This is used to check this so we do not need to create a clone with sub_state.

defs.docs: Consumes and merges the AssignState into this. Return true if a key was overwritten

defs.name: will_overwrite
defs.docs: Checks if the two AssignStates overlap. Not very good if they do. Check before merge

defs.name: SPPath
defs.docs:
The SPPath is used for identifying all objects in a model. The path will be defined
 based on where the item is in the model hierarchy

returns the next name in the path of this SPPath based on a path

returns the next name in the path based on a local or gloabl path

defs.name: SPNode
defs.docs:
The SPNode is tracking the name and the local and global path of an item
 The SPNode should be wrapped inside the item struct and the item should
 also impl the Noder trait.
